.TH "ccwgroup_create_dev" 9 "ccwgroup_create_dev" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ccwgroup_create_dev \- create and register a ccw group device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ccwgroup_create_dev
.BI "(struct device *parent "  ","
.BI "struct ccwgroup_driver *gdrv "  ","
.BI "int num_devices "  ","
.BI "const char *buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "parent" 12
parent device for the new device
.IP "gdrv" 12
driver for the new group device
.IP "num_devices" 12
number of slave devices
.IP "buf" 12
buffer containing comma separated bus ids of slave devices
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create and register a new ccw group device as a child of \fIparent\fP. Slave
devices are obtained from the list of bus ids given in \fIbuf\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success and an error code on failure.
.SH "CONTEXT"
non-atomic
